<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06032i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06032i">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06032i"> 32(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Probably died young / spared no efforts / learn his fate</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&lsquo;Sir Samuel Ferguson&rsquo; George Fox <mark>probably died young</mark>. &ldquo;He left Belfast to push his fortunes in British Guiana,&rdquo; writes Lady Ferguson in her memoirs of her husband, and no doubt succumbed to its unhealthy climate. His youthful friends heard no more of him. They <mark>spared no efforts, through a long series of years, to learn his fate</mark>. <small> Alfred Perceval Graves, <a name="ILMS2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ILMS2"><cite title="source">Irish Literary and Musical Studies</cite></a>, (1913) 40</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
